Are batters more successful if they see more pitches?

We can import 2024 data directly from statcast url. Among other things, this data provides total plate appearances, total pitches seen, as well as hitting performance statistics such as batting average, ops, and woba.

url <- "https://baseballsavant.mlb.com/leaderboard/custom?year=2024&type=batter&filter=&min=400&selections=player_age%2Cab%2Cpa%2Chit%2Csingle%2Cdouble%2Ctriple%2Chome_run%2Cstrikeout%2Cwalk%2Ck_percent%2Cbb_percent%2Cbatting_avg%2Cslg_percent%2Con_base_percent%2Con_base_plus_slg%2Cb_hit_by_pitch%2Cb_intent_walk%2Cwoba%2Cxwoba%2Csweet_spot_percent%2Cbarrel_batted_rate%2Chard_hit_percent%2Cavg_best_speed%2Cavg_hyper_speed%2Cpitch_count%2Cwhiff_percent%2Cswing_percent&chart=false&x=player_age&y=player_age&r=no&chartType=beeswarm&sort=xwoba&sortDir=desc"
curl <- paste0(url,"&csv=true")
df <- read.csv(curl)

We add a pitches per plate appearance column:

df <- df |> mutate(pitches_per_PA = pitch_count/pa)

Does pitches per plate appearance associate with batting average?

p <- ggplot(df,aes(x = pitches_per_PA,y=batting_avg))+

NFL Point Differential and Team Wins

The following code loads team info from a csv file linked on our course resource page, then makes a point plot. Team labels are added using the geom_text_repel() command which uses the ggrepel library.

nfl24 <- read.csv("https://mphitchman.com/stats/sports/data/nfl24_standings.csv")

ggplot(nfl24,aes(x = PD, y = W))+
  geom_text_repel(aes(label = Tm))+
  geom_point(col='seagreen')+
  geom_smooth(method='lm', formula=y~x, se = FALSE)+
  labs(x = 'point differential',
       y = 'wins',
       title = 'NFL 2024 Team wins vs point differential')

cor(nfl24$W,nfl24$PD)
## [1] 0.9073223
model <- lm(W ~ PD, data = nfl24)
summary(model)

Career Trajectory in MLB (Ch 7 of ABDR3e)

We use the tidyverse and Lahman packages to run the code below.

First we load the batting data and create a get_stats() function to extract a players age each season as well as their home run rate and a few other statistics.

batting <- Batting |>
  replace_na(list(SF = 0, HBP = 0))

get_stats <- function(player_id) {
  batting |> 
    filter(playerID == player_id) |>
    inner_join(People, by = "playerID") |>
    mutate(
      birthyear = if_else(
        birthMonth >= 7, birthYear + 1, birthYear
      ),
      Age = yearID - birthyear,
      SLG = (H + X2B + 2 * X3B + 3 * HR) / AB,
      OBP = (H + BB + HBP) / (AB + BB + HBP + SF),
      OPS = SLG + OBP,
      HRpct = HR / AB
    ) |>
    select(Age, SLG, OBP, OPS,HRpct)
}

Load a few careers

ruth <- get_stats("ruthba01") 
mantle <- get_stats("mantlmi01") 
mays <- get_stats("mayswi01") 
griff <- get_stats("griffke02")

all4 <- rbind(ruth |> mutate(player='ruth'), mantle |> mutate(player='mantle'), mays |> mutate(player = 'mays'), griff |> mutate(player="griffey"))

Lets look at each players season home run rate by age

ggplot(all4,aes(x=Age,y=HRpct))+
  geom_point()+
  facet_grid(~ player)

The following function fits a quadratic model to a given players HRpct stats by age.

fit_model <- function(d) {
  fit <- lm(HRpct ~ I(Age - 30) + I((Age - 30)^2), data = d)
  b <- coef(fit)
  Age_max <- 30 - b[2] / b[3] / 2
  Max <- b[1] - b[2] ^ 2 / b[3] / 4
  list(fit = fit, Age_max = Age_max, Max = Max)
}

Build the model for Ken Griffey Jr.

F2 <- fit_model(griff)
F2 |>
  pluck("fit") |>
  coef()
##     (Intercept)     I(Age - 30) I((Age - 30)^2) 
##    0.0808064088   -0.0013150766   -0.0005129373

Peak HR_pct and age, predicted by the model:

c(F2$Age_max, F2$Max)
## I(Age - 30) (Intercept) 
## 28.71809219  0.08164931

A visual:

ggplot(griff, aes(x = Age, y = HRpct)) + geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(
    method = "lm", se = FALSE, linewidth = 1.5,
    formula = y ~ poly(x, 2, raw = TRUE)
  ) +
  geom_vline(
    xintercept = F2$Age_max, 
    linetype = "dashed", color = "red"
  ) +
  geom_hline(
    yintercept = F2$Max,
    linetype = "dashed", color = "red"
  ) +
  annotate(
    geom = "text", x = c(30, 20), y = c(0.025, 0.075),
    label = c("Peak age", "Max"), size = 5,
    color = "red"
  ) + 
  ggtitle("Ken Griffey Jr. HR_pct by age, quadratic fit")
